cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM

The paper proposes a deep learning-based approach for indexing and retrieving 3D human skeletal data, which involves learning a motion descriptor using a deep network. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of trajectory cues and inter-class similarity, which suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. Additionally, the paper deals with 3D data and motion analysis, which could fall under the graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
